OL,3,CMost Blue Islands' customers should
OL,4,Cget money back, says travel expert
OL,6,F"It means that the card issuer accepts
OL,7,Fjoint liability with the merchant - in
OL,8,Fthis case Blue Islands - to deliver
OL,9,Fthe service.
OL,11,F"And if they don't, well, you get your
OL,12,Fmoney back."
OL,14,FIf flights were booked using a credit
OL,15,Fcard, then most terms and conditions
OL,16,Finclude protection under Section 75 of
OL,17,Fthe UK Consumer Credit Act 1974.
