OL,3,CMost Blue Islands' customers should
OL,4,Cget money back, says travel expert
OL,6,FHe explains: "There will be some
OL,7,Fpeople who book through agents, for
OL,8,Fwhom it will be a bit more complicated.
OL,10,F"But I think the big problem will be
OL,11,Fthat people who got a good deal with
OL,12,FBlue Islands might find replacement
OL,13,Fflights to be a lot more expensive."
OL,15,FThose with Blue Islands' gift vouchers
OL,16,Fare less likely to get their money
OL,17,Fback, as they are usually not
OL,18,Fprotected and will rank low on the
OL,19,Flist of priorities during the
OL,20,Fliquidation process.
